          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to validate preloaded billing data by comparing it against a coversheet record for a specific billing period. It aggregates billing amounts, therms, and CCF (hundred cubic feet) from two tables: "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "UploadConEdisonAccountPreload",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " and "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "UploadConEdisonCancellationPreload",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". The procedure then checks if these aggregated values match the corresponding values in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "ConEdCoversheet",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table for the current billing period. If there is a mismatch, it raises an error."
        }
